<article id="post-406" class="post-406 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-careers category-general category-travel tag-bars tag-business tag-chicago tag-critical-mass tag-illinois tag-usa">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/02/mercedes-benz-team-building/" rel="bookmark">Mercedes-Benz meetings, team building</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Allard and I hit the restaurant in the main atrium for breakfast, joined shortly thereafter by Christian and a very tired-looking Jules. Powdered eggs aren&#8217;t exactly the breakfast of champions. Jules has been up late working on presentations for today. Allard and I are thankfully exempt from any actual presentations. We&#8217;re more or less along for the ride.<br />
Actually, me more than Allard. Allard, at least, is the Technical Director. He needs to be there because the client knows who he is. He needs to be there because some of MBIT will be there. Why do *I* need to be there? Well, I can&#8217;t say for sure, because I really don&#8217;t know, but I think it comes down to the Client-Side Rearchitecture project that I&#8217;m spearheading, and that Allard won&#8217;t be here tomorrow (he&#8217;s only here for a day).<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2005/02/mercedes-benz-team-building/#more-406" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Mercedes-Benz meetings, team building&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
